node.text:
Without you we would not be here building our new HQ from the ground up. Sooo, we wanted to commemorate getting the presses up and running, with our very first print out of the new HQ dedicated to ALL of you!!! 

From the Ground Up, you helped us build this and we wanted you to feel like an official part of our team! We can’t thank you enough for supporting us throughout the years and believing in our brand and our message. 

❤️ Love, 
Dana, @killrobbailey , and the entire @flagnorfail TEAM

Do it anyway. Mighty shoulder veins at the end thoo 👀.
-
If you don’t have a decline bench, this is a great alternative, keeping your hips high in a glute bridge. Don’t bounce off the ground. I stop dead on every Rep. Then go right into flys, rotating so your pinkies touch at the top for a deep contraction. This is really where the shoulders were poppin!
-
More tips and my daily workouts, join the #dlbdaily (link in bio) ⬆️

node.text:
In the mornings we do weird stuff.  But this is the shit that makes me feel like an athlete.  You can barbell press probably all day, but can you take this big, round, heavy object that is the same size as you and get it from ground to overhead and control it? This is what builds tht different kind of strength.  It took me the entire workout to figure out my technique to get this tire up over my head without assistance.  I tried a bunch of “log pressing” techniques but finally ended on this one which is more of  thee ol’ “heeve ho.” I love a challenge.  But I love even more working on something for a while, then finally getting it!
 
If you got a HEAVY tire at home…GIVE THIS A TRY!!!
-
ALSO you can WIN that SXS on track in the background…go to @flagnorfail for details how to win my SXS!!!
- 
PS how cute is kaia at the end??!!

node.text:
1️⃣Low to High Cable Fly
2️⃣Cable Around the Worlds
3️⃣Declined Push-up
-
It’s very rare that I do a single exercise by itself. Unless it’s a big compound movement like a bench press, squat, dead, shoulder press or heavy rows... everything is always combined with at least one other exercise. This was my favorite little upper chest and shoulder pumping tri-set from yesterday #dlbdaily CHELTS workout. If you like volume and huge shoulder pumps, give this a try!!! And join the #dlbdaily (link in bio!)

🔥3 ROUNDS🔥: 
* DB Strict Shoulder Press (6-8 reps)
* DB Push Press (5-6 reps)
* DB Lateral Raise Drop Set (10 drop 10)
* Resistance Band Lateral Raise Pulses (AMRAP)
* Chest Support DB Reverse Fly (10-12 reps)
* Chest Support High/Wide Row (10-12 reps)
-
Today’s #DLBdaily Shoulder day was absolute fire 🔥!! If you want to see the FULL workout which will only take you 30 mins and you only need dumbbells and a barbell, Go to the link in my bio under #dlbdaily ⬆️⬆️⬆️. Your shoulders will thank me later 💪🏼💪🏼

node.text:
You know the quote, “everyone wants to ride the train, but not everyone wants to lay the tracks.” Laying tracks is long, hard, grueling, monotonous work.  Laying railroad tie after railroad tie, just doing the same thing over and over and over, until you finally get somewhere. 
-
This is the same.  Every single day. But I want to ride the train, so ima build that track. 
-
Just a view pics from today’s training. FULL #dlbdaily Back Day video up on my YouTube (link in bio) ⬆️ Make sure to go check that out!!

-

node.text: #shreddedallsummer  If I do another #dlbdaily 6 week Challenge to finish out summer… WHO’s IN ?!!! 🙋🏻‍♀️ or 🙅🏻‍♀️

FULL SHOULDER WORKOUT: give this workout a try. If this doesn’t blow your delts up, then I don’t know what will….

1️⃣ 4x 8-10 each
TRX y raise
TRX reverse fly
TRX W raise
TRX Row
-
2️⃣ 4 x 8-10 each
Cable Y Front Raise
Cable Upright Row
Cable Lying facepull
Cable high row
-
3️⃣ 4 rounds
DB Strict press - 6
DB Push Press - 6
DB Rotational shoulder press- 8-10
Dumbbell jammer- fail
-
4️⃣ 4 rounds
Lateral Raise Drop set - 10 drop 10
Band pulsing laterals to failure 
5️⃣ 3sets x 45 reps 
15 top half reps
15 bottom half Reps
5 regular 
5 holds
5 regular 
-
DED ☠️ #dlbdaily

node.text:
AND the WINNER of the  #dlbshreddedsummer Challenge and a check for $10,000 goes to………..Jessie Clifton!!!
-
Make sure to go watch the full YouTube video (link in bio) and get to know Jessie and what got him through this 6 week Transformation on top. Jessie has a great story. It hasn’t been the easiest for him these last 2 years. But, he saw an opportunity with this challenge and ran full speed at it and came out on top. And now it’s my opportunity to help him and his family get their feet back underneath them. Feels good. Feels like it was meant to be! Life can be hard. But sometimes when it’s the hardest, that’s your time to focus on you. Excited for your future Jessie!!! 
-
And don’t you guys worry, we will do this again!! It was so inspiring for me to see every single one of you making progress with yourselves. I hope this challenge was a kickstart to a fitter and healthier you and hopefully it didn’t end when the challenge ended. Let’s keep these habits going and keep making progress daily together!!! 
-
CONGRATS Jessie!!! And Congrats to all of you the complete the #dlbshreddedsummer Challenge!
